---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---
<MainLayout
  title="About GameOverGear"
  description="How GameOverGear researches retro gaming gear: published specs, aggregated verified-buyer reviews, independent testing, and use-case fit."
>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc-header">
      <span class="doc-kicker">About</span>
      <h1>About GameOverGear</h1>
      <p class="doc-lede">
        GameOverGear is an independent site that compares retro gaming gear by
        spec and use case, so the setup you rebuild is the one that feels right.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>
      We cover the hardware: controllers, arcade sticks, emulation handhelds,
      displays, scalers, cables, and the gift-y extras. We rank the gear, not
      the game. Every piece starts from one question: who is this actually the
      right fit for, and what hardware does it work with?
    </p>

    <h2>How we research</h2>
    <p>
      Our recommendations are research-based. We synthesize three kinds of
      evidence into use-case-fit picks:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Published specifications.</strong> Manufacturer spec sheets,
        latency figures, supported consoles and regions, panel and chip details,
        read carefully and compared across brands.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aggregated verified-buyer reviews.</strong> Patterns across owner
        reviews on Amazon and enthusiast forums, including the critical ones,
        cited to their source.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Independent testing.</strong> Third-party teardowns and measured
        results from outlets like My Life in Gaming, RetroRGB, and Modern Vintage
        Gamer, cited where we lean on them.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We do not claim personal hands-on testing in our content. We are explicit
      about that. If you want a first-person review, look for a reviewer who
      claims one. What we offer instead is careful comparison: spec analysis,
      aggregated owner reports, and honest use-case fit. You can read exactly how
      we weigh a product on our <a href="/how-we-evaluate/">how we evaluate</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      We earn affiliate commissions when you buy through our links. It does not
      change the price you pay, and it does not change which product we recommend.
      We do not accept payment in exchange for positive coverage. Full details are
      in our <a href="/disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Specs change and listings drift. If something is out of date or wrong, tell
      us on the <a href="/contact/">contact</a> page and we will fix it.
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .doc { max-width: var(--content-wide); margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6) var(--space-20); }
  .doc-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .doc-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    color: var(--color-paper-ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .doc-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .doc h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .doc p { font-family: var(--font-sans); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); color: var(--color-paper-ink); }
  .doc ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: var(--space-5) 0; }
  .doc li {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    padding: 16px 22px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brass);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-paper-ink);
  }
  .doc li strong { color: var(--color-brass); }
  .doc a { color: var(--color-brass); }
</style>
